{{mineral-stub}}

'''Alison Kellow'''  is a botanist and research scientist from Australia, and a lecturer at [[La Trobe University]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://www.nhbs.com/an-illustrated-guide-to-new-zealand-hebes-book|title=An Illustrated Guide to New Zealand Hebes|website=www.nhbs.com|language=en-US|access-date=2017-10-03}}</ref><ref name=":1" />

Kellow completed a Bachelor of Science degree at the [[University of Melbourne]], and postgraduate studies in environmental science at [[Monash University]]. She completed her doctoral degree in Natural Resource Sciences at the [[University of Adelaide]].<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=http://www.latrobe.edu.au/she/staff/profile?uname=akellow|title=Staff profile|last=University|first=La Trobe|website=www.latrobe.edu.au|language=en|access-date=2017-10-03}}</ref>

Kellow is the joint author, with Michael Bayly, of ''An Illustrated Guide to New Zealand Hebes''''',''' which was a finalist in the 2007 [[Montana New Zealand Book Awards]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/entertainment/news/article.cfm?c_id=1501119&objectid=10443112|title=Posthumous nominations for authors in Montana book awards|date=2007-06-01|work=NZ Herald|access-date=2017-10-03|language=en-NZ|issn=1170-0777}}</ref> The pair worked on the project while both were researchers for the [[Museum of New Zealand Te Papa Tongarewa]].<ref name=":0" /> Kellow also held a position at Industrial Research Ltd, working on [[Flavonoid|flavonoid chemistry]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rnzih.org.nz/pages/hebe.htm|title=RNZIH - Horticulture Pages - Hebe|website=www.rnzih.org.nz|access-date=2017-10-03}}</ref>

