{{Infobox company | name = Association for the Study of the Cuban Economy | logo = ASCE_logo_220.png | logo_size = 250px | caption = | type = Not-for-profit | ge\nre = | foundation = [[United States]] (1990) | founder = | location_city = [[Washington, D.C.]] | location_country = | location = | locations = | area_served = | key_people = | industry = | products = | services = Economic reports, conferences | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | owner = | num_employees = | parent = | divisions = | subsid = | slogan = | homepage = [http://www.ascecuba.org/ www.ascecuba.org/] | footnotes = | intl = }}
The '''Association for the Study of the Cuban Economy (ASCE)''' is a professional association for the study of the [[Economy of Cuba|Cuban economy]].<ref name = "ASCE history">{{Cite web |title= Notes on the History of The Association for the Study of the Cuban Economy |url= http://www.ascecuba.org/about/history/ |publisher= ascecuba.org |accessdate= 26 March 2012 }}</ref> The association was [[Incorporation (business)|incorporated]] on 3 August 1990 by Cuban American economists interested in the post-[[Cold War]] prospects for [[Cuba]].
