'''Barré Glacier''' is a channel [[glacier]] about {{convert|5|nmi|km|0}} wide and 5 nautical miles long, flowing north from the continental ice to the coast close east of [[Cape Pepin]]. It was delineated from air photos taken by [[U.S. Navy Operation Highjump]], 1946–47, and was named by the [[Advisory Committee on Antarctic Names]] for [[Michel Barré]], leader of the [[French Antarctic Expedition]] wintering party of 1951–52, whose party extended reconnaissance of the coastal features as far west as this glacier.<ref name=gnis/>

