[[File:Bernard Cracroft Aston 1907.jpg|thumb|upright|Aston in 1907]]
'''Bernard Cracroft Aston''' {{post-nominals|country=NZL|CBE}} (9 August 1871 &ndash; 31 May 1951) was a New Zealand agricultural chemist and botanist. He was born in [[Beckenham]], [[Kent]], England, on 9 August 1871. He was a member of the [[1907 Sub-Antarctic Islands Scientific Expedition]].<ref name="DNZB Aston">{{DNZB|last=Bailey|first=R. W.|id=3a23|title=Bernard Cracroft Aston|accessdate=23 April 2017}}</ref> He was appointed a [[Order of the British Empire|Commander of the Order of the British Empire]] in the [[1949 New Year Honours (New Zealand)|1949 New Year Honours]] for services to agriculture and botany.<ref>{{London Gazette |issue=38494 |date=31 December 1948 |page=34 |supp=y }}</ref>

