{{Italic title}} {{Taxobox | name = ''Entomoplasma freundtii'' | regnum = [[Bacteria]] | phylum = [[Tenericutes]] | classis = [[Mollicutes]] | ordo = [[Entomoplasmatales]] | familia = Entomoplasmataceae | genus = ''Entomoplasma'' | species = ''E. freundtii'' | binomial = ''Entomoplasma freundtii'' | binomial_authority = [[Joseph G. Tully|Tully]] et al. 1998 | subdivision_ranks = Subspecies | subdivision = }}
'''''Entomoplasma freundtii''''' is a mollicute bacteria species that can be isolated from the green tiger beetle (''[[Cicindela campestris]]'', Coleoptera: Cicindelidae).<ref>{{Cite journal|pmid=9828421|year=1998|last1=Tully|first1=JG|last2=Whitcomb|first2=RF|last3=Hackett|first3=KJ|last4=Williamson|first4=DL|last5=Laigret|first5=F|last6=Carle|first6=P|last7=Bové|first7=JM|last8=Henegar|first8=RB|last9=Ellis|first9=NM|last10=Dodge|first10=DE|last11=Adams|first11=J|title=''Entomoplasma freundtii'' sp. nov., a new species from a green tiger beetle (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae)|volume=48|pages=1197–204|journal=International Journal of Systematic Bacteriology|doi=10.1099/00207713-48-4-1197|issue=4}}</ref>
