{{italic title}}
'''''In simulacra''''' is a [[Latin language|Latin]] phrase meaning "within likenesses." The phrase is used similarly to ''[[in vivo]]'' or ''[[ex vivo]]'' to denote the context of an experiment. In this case, the phrase denotes that the experiment is not conducted in the actual subject, but rather a [[Scientific modelling|model]] of such.

==See also==
*[[List of Latin phrases]]

