{{Infobox Nuclear weapons test |name = Upshot-Knothole Dixie |picture = Upshot-Knothole Dixie 001.jpg |picture_description = |country = United States |test_series = [[Operation Upshot–Knothole]] |test_site = [[Nevada Test Site]] |date = April 6, 1953 |test_type = [[Nuclear weapons testing#Types|Atmospheric]] |yield = 11 [[TNT equivalent|kt]] |previous_test = [[Upshot-Knothole Ruth]] |next_test = [[Upshot-Knothole Ray]] }}
'''Upshot-Knothole Dixie''' was the fourth test-firing of [[Operation Upshot–Knothole]], an atomic weapons test series conducted in 1953 by the United States at the [[Nevada Test Site]].
Upshot-Knothole Dixie was an 11-kiloton airdrop shot which detonated at 6,000 feet altitude, the highest [[air burst]] detonation conducted to that date.
