A '''voice message'''<ref>{{cite news|last1=Dipali|first1=K|title=Business voice message answer service|url=http://www.msg2txt.com.au/msg2txt-office.php|accessdate=4 November 2015|agency=msg2txt|publisher=msg2txt|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160219041640/http://www.msg2txt.com.au/msg2txt-office.php|archive-date=19 February 2016|dead-url=yes|df=dmy-all}}</ref> is a message containing audio of a person's voice. Voice itself could be 'packaged' and sent through the IP backbone so that it reaches its marked 'address'. In a technical sense, the process of sending 'voice packets' is a semi passive way of communication. However, given the speed at which it could be delivered can make the communication sound seamless.
==See also== *[[CDMA]] *[[IP telephony]] *[[Voicemail]] *[[VoIP]]
